<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
     <!-- css link -->
     <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
       <!-- bootstrap link -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">

    <!-- icon -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.2/css/all.min.css">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- header -->
    <%- include('./header.ejs') %>
     <!-- header end -->


    <section>
        <img src="/images/aboutHeroImage.webp" class="aboutHeroImage">
    </section>

    
    <!-- hero -->
    <section id="aboutHero">
        <div class="container">

            
            <div class="px-4 py-5 mt-5 text-center">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-body-emphasis">Lets Learn About Us</h1>
                <div class="col-lg-6 mx-auto">
                    <p class="lead mb-4">Becoming a proficient front-end developer is a journey of many steps. It begins with a solid foundation in the basic languages, an understanding of version control, and a gradual exploration of sophisticated tools. It’s complemented by a design-thinking approach, empathy for the user, and an insatiable hunger for growth and learning.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="container col-xxl-8 px-4 pb-5">
            <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-body-emphasis lh-1 mb-3 text-center">Front-end vs. Back-end  </h1> 
            <div class="row flex-lg-row-reverse align-items-center g-5 py-5">
              <div class="col-10 col-sm-8 col-lg-6">
                <img src="/images/aboutImage2.png" class="d-block mx-lg-auto img-fluid" alt="Bootstrap Themes" width="700" height="500" loading="lazy">
              </div>
              <div class="col-lg-6">
                
                <p class="lead">There are two paths towards becoming a web developer: the back-end or the front-end. Back-end developers build server-side software. They’re responsible for all the performance, stability, security and speed of your site or app, all of which power the front-end or user-facing side.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
    </section>
    <!-- End Hero -->

     
    <!-- hero -->
    <section id="aboutHero">
        

        <div class="container col-xxl-8 px-4 pb-5">
            <div class="row flex-lg-row-reverse align-items-center g-5 py-5">
             
              <div class="col-lg-6">
                <p class="lead">Front-end developers, on the other hand, get to build everything a user touches and interacts with on the screen, such as layouts, information, engagement, etc. Front-end developers are both creative and tech-savvy, and act as the bridge between designers and back-end programmers.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="col-10 col-sm-8 col-lg-6">
                <img src="/images/aboutBackendImage.png" class="d-block mx-lg-auto img-fluid" alt="Bootstrap Themes" width="700" height="500" loading="lazy">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          
    </section>
    <!-- End Hero -->

    <%- include('./footer.ejs') %>
